The paper deals with algorithms for finding maximum subarrays, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.AL). The use of divide-and-conquer techniques suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG) or divide-and-conquer algorithms (cs.DC). Additionally, the paper presents a new algorithm for finding the k largest sums of X + Y, which involves selecting the kth smallest number in an array, indicating that it may also fall under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
